items.name: Minecraftmodcustomstuff Wiki
items.title: Minecraftmodcustomstuff Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft wiki!
items.desc: Custom Stuff is a Minecraft mod developed by CubeX2 that allows for the addition of blocks and items into the game without having to code java. By using a basic mockup you can add a variety of common things to the game including blocks, ores, tools, and so-forth. With a little knowledge of javascript you can also create many more impressive things such as crops and even trees! If you've ever wanted to create a Minecraft mod but didn't want to learn java to do it, this mod is for you!

items.name: Awesome Stuff Wiki
items.title: Awesome Stuff Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Awesome Stuff Wiki :P
items.desc:
Anyone can contribute to this wiki. Add pages about -
1) Music (Write about bands, singers, genres of music)

2) Food (Write about different types of food and drinks that you like)

3) Books (Write about your favorite books)

4) Movies (Write about movies you enjoy)

5) Characters (Write about your favorite characters from books, movies, TV shows. Cartoon or real)

6) TV shows (Write about your favorite series' and cartoons)

7) People (Write about famous people. Dead or alive. They can be from bands or they can be actors)

8) Anime! (Anime and manga TV series, comics or characters)

9) Other random stuff you like!

items.name: The universe of made up stuff Wiki
items.title: The universe of made up stuff Wiki
items.headline: The ultimate fanon wiki
items.desc: This wiki is for absolutely anything made up that could ever possibly exist. Want to let the world know about a character you've made? Not anywhere to put it? Think again. Here! Got a little story you've written, want to let people see it? Over here, then. Just think…this wiki is for any series. New series could be created here, and then wikis about those could be made. This could happen many times, and therefore…internet revolution! To help this happen, check out this wiki and be helpful by adding a page.
